When I'm listening, if I were to
ever listen, I actually, at

00:34:47.510 --> 00:34:49.940
this point now, I feel like I've
gotten old, but I really

00:34:49.940 --> 00:34:51.020
do like classical music.

00:34:51.020 --> 00:34:53.699
Because my dad loves classical,
so there's a lot of

00:34:53.699 --> 00:34:56.670
fond memories when I listen
to certain things.

00:34:56.670 --> 00:34:59.710
I have a couple CDs that
I'll stick in the

00:34:59.710 --> 00:35:01.135
thing, whatever it is.

00:35:01.135 --> 00:35:02.800
But I'm not really
a music person.

00:35:02.800 --> 00:35:03.920
SANDRA LEUNG LI: It sounds
like we need to work on

00:35:03.920 --> 00:35:05.170
getting you headphones.

00:35:07.070 --> 00:35:08.320
What do you do for fun?

00:35:11.980 --> 00:35:13.230
JOANNE CHANG: I love going
out to eat with

00:35:13.230 --> 00:35:15.010
Christopher and friends.

00:35:15.010 --> 00:35:16.995
That's definitely something that
I enjoy a lot and look

00:35:16.995 --> 00:35:19.290
forward to when we can
schedule it in.

00:35:19.290 --> 00:35:21.400
I still run and exercise
every day, which

00:35:21.400 --> 00:35:22.460
might sound not fun.

00:35:22.460 --> 00:35:24.530
But for me, it's very fun.

00:35:24.530 --> 00:35:26.645
I love to read.

00:35:26.645 --> 00:35:28.510
I don't have enough time
to just sit and relax.

00:35:28.510 --> 00:35:32.180
So my ideal is on Sunday
mornings to wake up and have

00:35:32.180 --> 00:35:35.170
breakfast with Christopher and
then just read the paper

00:35:35.170 --> 00:35:38.890
slowly over the course
of the day.

00:35:38.890 --> 00:35:39.390
Yeah.

00:35:39.390 --> 00:35:41.240
Those are the three things
that I like to do.

00:35:41.240 --> 00:35:44.542
I like to shop, but I don't
spend a lot of time shopping.

00:35:44.542 --> 00:35:45.820
SANDRA LEUNG LI: Oh.

00:35:45.820 --> 00:35:49.670
And the last question, I noticed
the Flour motto to

00:35:49.670 --> 00:35:50.800
"Make Life Sweeter.

00:35:50.800 --> 00:35:54.920
Eat Dessert First." So do you
really eat dessert first?

00:35:54.920 --> 00:35:56.615
JOANNE CHANG: Well, I'm
kind of eating a

00:35:56.615 --> 00:35:57.470
dessert all day long.

00:35:57.470 --> 00:36:01.040
So by the time I get to dinner,
I actually feel like I

00:36:01.040 --> 00:36:02.410
need to eat some food.

00:36:02.410 --> 00:36:04.760
I'm very conscious of the fact
that I don't eat real food

00:36:04.760 --> 00:36:07.030
usually until dinner time.

00:36:07.030 --> 00:36:12.320
But on days that I'm not at
the bakery, I think it's

00:36:12.320 --> 00:36:14.960
important to eat dessert
first, because you

00:36:14.960 --> 00:36:15.690
might not have room.

00:36:15.690 --> 00:36:18.670
I've had plenty of dinners where
I've run out of room by

00:36:18.670 --> 00:36:19.340
the end of the dinner.

00:36:19.340 --> 00:36:21.620
So if I can, I try
to sneak it in.

00:36:21.620 --> 00:36:22.250
It's a little odd.

00:36:22.250 --> 00:36:23.230
SANDRA LEUNG LI: Love
that strategy.

00:36:23.230 --> 00:36:23.985
JOANNE CHANG: Sometimes
the servers are

00:36:23.985 --> 00:36:25.450
like, are you sure?

00:36:25.450 --> 00:36:28.460
But we've seen customers at
Myers and Chang do that.

00:36:28.460 --> 00:36:33.130
They'll order the nasi goreng
and the arctic char roll and

00:36:33.130 --> 00:36:34.040
coconut cream pie.

00:36:34.040 --> 00:36:35.400
And I'm always like,
are you sure?

00:36:35.400 --> 00:36:39.560
And they're like, yeah, we want
to eat dessert as well.

00:36:39.560 --> 00:36:39.784
SANDRA LEUNG LI: Cool.

